File_Description: Data package level readme. Contains data package summary; critical information; acknowledgements; and contact information.

File-level metadata that lists and describes all of the files contained in the data package. Two copies of the flmd have been included in this data package: one outside of the data zip folder and one inside. The purpose of this duplicated file is for the user to see the data package contents without downloading and unzipping the data folder; while still maintaining a complete set of files inside the zip.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021); ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for File-level Metadata (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Data dictionary that defines columns headers across all csv files contained in the data package.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Respiration rates calculated from time series dissolved oxygen data measured from laboratory incubations of sediment and unfiltered stream surface water. The calculation used to produce some of these data (theoretical respiration rates) includes assumptions that the project team has decided are appropriate; but the user should decide if using this data is appropriate for their analysis. See method codes for more detail.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Sediment total organic carbon and total nitrogen content.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Sediment bacterial abundance (total bacteria; total phototrophs; total heterotrophs).
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Sediment grain size distribution measured from the less than 2 millimeter fraction of sediment.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Sediment carbon and nitrogen stable isotope data.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Respiration rates calculated from time series dissolved oxygen data measured from laboratory incubations of sediment and then normalized to sediment volume in the incubation vials. The calculation used to produce some of these data (theoretical respiration rates) includes assumptions that the project team has decided are appropriate; but the user should decide if using this data is appropriate for their analysis. See "WHONDRS_S19S_Sediment_Normalized_Respiration_Methods.txt" for more detail.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Sediment dissolved organic carbon (DOC, measured as non-purgeable organic carbon, NPOC) data from both the “Sed_Field” and “SED_INC” samples. See readme for more information about the difference between these samples.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Wet sediment mass; dry sediment mass; water mass; and wet sediment volume in incubation vial.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: The R code used to calculate respiration rates from the time series dissolved oxygen data.
Brief description of the R code and input file used to calculate respiration rates from time series dissolved oxygen data.
Plots of time series dissolved oxygen data and incubation time.
Time series dissolved oxygen data used to calculate respiration rates.
Brief description of file structure and methods associated with FTICR-MS data.
Instructions to calibrate and align the FTICR-MS data.
R script to process FTICR-MS data.
Calibration file needed to process FTICR-MS data.

Raw FTICR-MS instrument files. The first asterisk * indicates sample ID. The second asterisk is the replicate indicator (U; M; or D) and the ion accumulation time (IAT) after the letter "p". Each sample had three replicates (Upstream; Midstream; Downstream). See readme for more information about the difference between these samples and the SED_INC samples.

Raw FTICR-MS instrument files. The first asterisk * indicates sample ID. The second asterisk is the replicate indicator (U; M; or D) and the ion accumulation time (IAT) after the letter "p". Each sample had three replicates (Upstream; Midstream; Downstream). See readme for more information about the difference between these samples and the Sed_Field samples.
Defines the codes used in the two lab tracker files. It contains a series of codes used to describe the methods and other pertinent information regarding sample processing.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Laboratory methods information for each incubation vial; including Sample_ID (with suffix and replicate indicators) and the appropriate methods code for each sample. Methods codes are defined in the Methods_Codes file.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Sample metadata including Sample_ID information for each vial used during the campaign and accompanying information captured in the field (i.e. coordinates; date; time; stream name; temperature; pH; SpC).
Step-by-step instructions used to complete the sampling in the field.
Laboratory methods information for total organic carbon, total nitrogen, and stable isotope analyses.
Laboratory methods information for all flow cytometry samples (bacterial abundance).
Laboratory methods information for all grain size samples.

File that maps between sample names and registered International Generic Sample Numbers (IGSNs). Includes metadata required by ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Sample ID and Metadata (Damerow et al. 2020). Some fields are repeated from the field metadata. In compliance with the ESS-DIVE Location Metadata Reporting Format (Crystal-Ornelas et al. 2022) the Submission_Contact_Name; Submission_Contact_Email; Location_ID; Description; Latitude; and Longitude can all be found in the Dataset Metadata associated with this data package (and found on the ESS-DIVE landing page). The Location_ID; Latitude; and Longitude can also be found in v2_CM_SSS_IGSN-Mapping.csv as Locality; Latitude; and Longitude; respectively. There is no separate file associated with the ESS-DIVE Location Metadata Reporting Format.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021); ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Sample ID and Metadata (Damerow et al. 2020); ESS-DIVE Location Metadata Reporting Format (Crystal-Ornelas et al. 2022)

File_Description: Laboratory methods information for each FTICR/NPOC vial; including  Sample_ID (with suffix and replicate indicators) and the appropriate methods code for each sample. It also contains additional laboratory processing and instrument information (i.e. dilutions; ion accumulation time). Methods codes are defined in the Methods_Codes file.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure (Velliquette et al. 2021)

File_Description: Laboratory methods information for normalized respiration.
Laboratory methods information for wet sediment mass; dry sediment mass; water mass; and wet sediment volume.
Laboratory methods information for all XRF samples.

File associated with each sample analyzed for XRF. "Multivariate statistical analysis" data. These files are generated to reduce the size of massive datasets by decomposing the XRF spectra to find energy features common to given spatial locations.
File associated with each sample analyzed for XRF. An extensive list of details and parameters of energy dispersive spectroscopy (EDS) analyses.
File associated with each sample analyzed for XRF. XRF details, parameters, and energy counts throughout the analyzed spectra.
Sediment elemental abundance from XRF.
